Commented on #1572 Spoolman integration does not support IP-camera streams

Unfortunately, my AXIS camera doesn't seem to support custom HTTP headers but I can confirm I am running into the same issue you're describing. What ended up working for me is the following:
Edit your NGINX configuration file /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/fluidd and add the following content before the last } : location /webcam-axis/ { postpone_output 0; (6 more lines were trimmed) Please check here for a full example
Run the following command on the host: service nginx reload Change the webcam URL in your fluidd settings to /webcam-axis/axis-cgi/jpg/image.cgi?camera=2 (no host name / ip address at the start!) try scanning a spool ;)
